venue_information: happy Mondays! Every monday night @ La3
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

event_location_details: En 1984 sobre las cenizas de la discoteca San Francisco voló por primera vez el murciélago más emblemático de la noche. Abría Spook Factory, el templo de la música Valenciana. Un espacio para la experimentación sensorial que marcó un antes y un después en la historia del clubbing. Hoy Spook sigue siendo historia viva de Valencia, ofreciendo una programación musical de vanguardia nacional e internacional. Todos los sábados desde las 18:00h a las 7:30h tienes una cita con la música, la catarsis y la vanguardia. Bandas, Lives, Dj’s, Foodtrucks y mucho más. #TodosLosSabadosUnFestival.

event_title: DOMINGO | WATEKE. Feel the sound in the city
venue_information: Wateke
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

Hostel Valencia, inaugurado en marzo de 2016 y situado en el centro de Valencia, en el interior de la estación de tren Nord de Valencia. Un nuevo concepto de alojamiento en el centro de la ciudad de Valencia, con conciertos en vivo, Snack-bar y el mejor ambiente, joven de Valencia! UP Hostel Valencia está situado en el centro de la ciudad de Valencia, dentro de la estación de tren del Norte, y al lado de la plaza de toros de Valencia y el Ayuntamiento. venue_information: Tuesday Party!
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

event_genres: Elegant, Cozy, House, Groove Techno, Minimal
venue_information: La Cuina is much more than an electronic music party. It is the natural evolution of the Music To Take Away brand, bringing house, groove and minimal to the most exclusive and captivating locations. At La Cuina, we have found our home, a fixed space that symbolizes the essence of a delivery, the dark kitchen: a place where the purest and most authentic musical experience is cooked, ready to be enjoyed by lovers of electronic music in its own form. Here, music is the main course and each event, a feast for the senses. In the fiery heart of Ruzafa, where the nights boil and creativity has no limits, La Cuina hides. This clandestine kitchen is for those who know what a real party is: pure slow-cooked electronic music. Get ready to savor the most exquisite house, from the groove that catches you to the minimal that envelops you. Each party is a custom-made tasting menu, where the beats are the main course and the dance floor is the table where it is served. Photos? No. Videos? Forget it. VIP or guest lists? Here the desire rules, not the name. Here you don't come to posturing, you come to enjoy the authentic recipe: party without filters, music without concessions, rhythm direct to the palate. What happens at La Cuina stays within its four walls: well-kept secrets, like grandma's recipe. Are you hungry? I hope, because at La Cuina, we don't leave anyone hungry.
event_location_details: Latex Club in Valencia presents itself as a dynamic and versatile space, which from now on opens its doors with a varied offer for each day of the week: Thursday: Moova - A party that mixes pop, hits, reggaeton, trap and electronic music, designed to adapt to all audiences. Moova is the new event in Ruzafa that promises to make you dance to the rhythm of all genres. Friday: Club Gordo is a unique experience in the Valencia techno scene, known for its focus on the total enjoyment of electronic music. It offers a night of techno and its most advanced variants, immersing attendees in an atmosphere of mystery and freedom. Saturdays: Four rotating proposals TBA Latex Club is thus positioned as an essential place in Valencia's nightlife, combining different styles and atmospheres to satisfy all music lovers.

event_title: VIERNES | WATEKE. Feel the sound in the city
venue_information: Wateke
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

event_location_details: En 1984 sobre las cenizas de la discoteca San Francisco voló por primera vez el murciélago más emblemático de la noche. Abría Spook Factory, el templo de la música Valenciana. Un espacio para la experimentación sensorial que marcó un antes y un después en la historia del clubbing. Hoy Spook sigue siendo historia viva de Valencia, ofreciendo una programación musical de vanguardia nacional e internacional. Todos los sábados desde las 18:00h a las 7:30h tienes una cita con la música, la catarsis y la vanguardia. Bandas, Lives, Dj’s, Foodtrucks y mucho más. #TodosLosSabadosUnFestival.

event_genres: Underground, Hard Techno, Melodic House & Techno
line_up: Andres Campo, Melanie Ribbe, Siles, Lucas Cabello, Sou Allen, Domen
venue_information: S — 7 — Diciembre. Barraca presenta su 59 Aniversario con Andres Campo y Melanie Ribbe La ya floreciente carrera de Andrés Campo está experimentando un rápido y espectacular ascenso. De convertirse en uno de los DJs y productores más queridos en España, su nombre es ahora sinónimo de talento, calidad y música emocionante, tanto como DJ, incluyendo su residencia en Florida 135 junto con muchos shows internacionales, y como productor, firmando con Drumcode, FilthOnAcid, Second State, Intec, Mood, Odd Recordings y Mindshake sólo en el último año.
event_location_details: With more than 50 years of history behind it, Barraca has been open since the summer of 1965. In the mid-80s its popularity rose due to the great electronic music movement that took place in Spain. The movement is known as "La Ruta del Bacalao", where they offered a host of festivals and festivals along the Spanish Mediterranean coast, especially the Valencian one. Barraca took advantage of the movement and positioned itself as one of the greatest exponents of this underground movement. Baracca is divided up into 4 rooms: - Circo: is the largest room, with a capacity for almost a thousand people, the place where the great events of Valencia are held. DJs ranking amongst Richie Hawtin, Laurent Garnier, Ricardo Villalobos and Danny Tenaglia have passed through the booth. No doubt, the best. - La Barraca: the original club underwent an impressive renovation in 2007 that has allowed it to continue offering the best electronic music in Valencia. - Showroom: this is your alternative room, where the young and rising names of techno and house host more experimental sessions. Dedicated to house music since its beginnings, its original name was simply, House Room. - Terraza: with a capacity of 600 people, it’s a venue to rival some of the best in Ibiza. During the summer, it’s always the first to open. It has a huge fan base and the coolest sounds of Valencia. Barraca has established itself as one of the most important underground clubs in Spain and hosts a lot of great sets by the most anticipated artists. With exactly 12,738 sessions and more than 21,400 DJs that have passed through the Valencian club, we can say that Barraca is not just a lot of good electronic music. Barraca is synonymous with quality. Barraca delivers the best techno and the best house in all its aspects. DJs and producers like Ricardo Villalobos, Loco Dice, Tania Vulcano, Marco Carola, Ellen Allien and Óscar Mulero are a clear example of this. The dress code is casual, informal, underground. With Xceed you can buy your early bird ticket for Barraca. Alternatively, you can buy it at the door on the night. Barraca is open at the weekends and the night before some holidays. Barraca opens its doors at 00:00 until 06:00 in the morning. The average price of entry is between 15€ and 25€.
event_ticket_types: Bottle Service, All night long Ticket + drink, Ticket + beer before 2:30AM
location_address: Calle Les Palmeres, Sueca, Valencia, Valencia, Spain

venue_information: More info soon.
event_location_details: Sound Factory nació en marzo del año 2000 cuando la sala que ocupaba el local donde estaba situada, por aquel entonces Rockola Pinedo, fue trasladada a otra ubicación, en este momento la sala de pinedo adquirió un nuevo nombre y pasó a llamarse «Factory Of Sound» algo más de 3 semanas, para que en Abril del año 2000 pasase a llamarse tal y como la conocimos, «Sound Factory». Siempre bajo la dirección de su maestro de ceremonias, Pedro Contreras, la sala permaneció abierta hasta el mes de Junio del año 2004, cuando cerró sus puertas definitivamente. De la sala tal y como se conoció, queda ya bien poco y es que al cierre de Sound Factory, esta fue abierta en varias ocasiones con distintos nombres y tipos de música, fue sala «Space Valencia» en el año 2008 hasta que en 2009 adquirió el nombre por el que actualmente la conocemos, «Spook Club Vlc». Por su cabina han pasado multitud de deejays pero los que hacen que el espíritu Factory se sienta allá donde van, son son Alfredo Pareja y David Cabeza, posteriormente se incorporaron al team djs Vicente Belenguer y German Bass. Si bien la discoteca cerró en 2004, desde entonces se vienen celebrando cada año 3 fiestas en honor a esta sala, Fallas, Summer Party y el Aniversario.
event_ticket_types: Segundo tramo, Primer Tramo, Tercer tramo, Primer Tramo - Zona Backstage

event_title: DOMINGO | WATEKE. Feel the sound in the city
venue_information: Wateke
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

event_title: Freddy K + Kaiser + Total w/ Fenrick
venue_information: Main: Freddy K + Kaiser + David Zona + Everynation Cubo / Total: Fenrick + Ariezzz + Kenyi
event_location_details: En 1984 sobre las cenizas de la discoteca San Francisco voló por primera vez el murciélago más emblemático de la noche. Abría Spook Factory, el templo de la música Valenciana. Un espacio para la experimentación sensorial que marcó un antes y un después en la historia del clubbing. Hoy Spook sigue siendo historia viva de Valencia, ofreciendo una programación musical de vanguardia nacional e internacional. event_title: SÁBADO TARDE | LOS TARDEOS DE LA3 | BULLET CLUB
venue_information: Bullet Club + La3 djs
event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

event_location_details: It’s been open for less than 10 years but La3 has quickly become one of the most iconic clubs in Valencia. This club boasts quality sound systems, which have recently been upgraded to the Funktion-One system. The club’s name comes from the 3 rooms within the club: Main Room, Oven Club y Sala2, which have hosted the most famous national and international artists such as Jeff Mills, Nina Kraviz, Laurent Garnier, Seth Troxler, 2manydjs, Vitalic and Flux Pavilion among many others. La3 is not only one of the best party clubs in Valencia but it is a meeting point for true music lovers. In terms of music, La3 is now adding more urban styles such as trap, R&B and hip-hop and the popular Friday night is adapting to the needs of its public, the young and cosmopolitan masses. To satisfy you on Saturday nights, there is a new event at the club called “Electric Saturdays”, where you can enjoy the best national and international techno and house DJs in any of the 3 rooms that the venue boasts. If La3 is known for something in particular, it’s because of its high quality music played weekend after weekend.

venue_information: Keep the night alive at the ultimate afterwork party on November 20th, starting at 21:00. Get ready for an unforgettable evening filled with music, good vibes and great company! Don’t miss out on the party at Chica Club! Grab your friends and dance the night away.
event_location_details: Chica Club is the latest evolution of the experience offered by Boca Grande and Boca Chica, crafted for those who appreciate the finer things in life—designed for the curious, the creative, the well-traveled, and those who just know. It’s a space where creators come together to be part of something special, and we’re beyond excited to have you join us on this journey. Chica Club is a place where vibrant energy meets exclusivity, drawing inspiration from iconic nightlife in cities like Paris and London. event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

event_title: JNJS All Night Long at Les Enfants
event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: Jay Nortown y Jacobo Saavedra se conocieron en Pikes en 2018, un buen lugar para comenzar una relación musical. They quickly connected their musical tastes and began a friendly relationship that was forged in the booth, with a great chemistry between them that they soon transferred to the studio. Their separate career have been very different, which makes them complement each other perfectly, which makes their sessions characterized by a very forceful character. They have a great dancefloor reading and do not hesitate to play with various styles close to minimal house. They are combined generating sensations on the track, counteracting ups and downs, breaks and melodies. Together they have played, besides many places in Ibiza, like Eden, Playa Soleil, Cova Santa or Octan, in places like Les Enfants, Jazzy (Madrid), Friedas Buexe (Switzerland), Fabric London, Marrakech with Supervibe and many more. In the studio, these disparate trajectories until they come together generate something special, just like in the booth. They understand music and the way of producing in very different ways, which means that when they come together and create a common workflow, they achieve great results, having a very characteristic sound, which can be seen in the different musical styles that they are capable of doing. His releases are very well received on the local and international scene. EPs on labels like Fun Records, El Row, HedZup and many more as well as several vinyl records, on labels like Moovin, UNK Milano or SVDR (the label they run) all Sold Out. Velvet is the new project in which they are investing all their energy. It will consist of a series of events, mainly in Ibiza (Eden and Nui), Fabric London, Madrid and Les Enfants, and a vinyl only record label, which will be supported by a series of edit and other releases on bandcamp. His music has been played by great artists from the minimal-house scene, such as Traumer, Nu Zau, Alci, Arapu, Janeret, Vern, Sepp, Tania Vulcano, Mihai Pol, Cally, Chklte, Direkt, 2Vilas, De La Swing, or Silat Beksi in places like Sunwaves, Circoloco, Pyramid, Space Miami, Fabric London, Music On and many more.

With a curated music line-up that encompasses emerging talent and international guests from the underground scene the downtown club has become the meeting point for electronic music lovers with a passion for the clean sound and solid sound systems.

event_title: HEROES ( Summer Heroes winter edition) with MOONKIZA, BMS CREW, Markuss at PACHA Red Room
venue_information: This winter we are not going to stay frozen! And we are going to become HEROES, yes We Can Be HEROES. We are getting ready so that in Barcelona the dancing and partying doesn't stop when the cold weather starts, and for this occasion we are moving from the Open Air to the indoor club. And for this, nothing more and nothing less than the RED ROOM of the legendary club PACHA. Yes, a winter of becoming HEROES is coming and for that we will go out with everything and with a local crew that is willing to put on the suit and go out to fight for your right to party. For this first edition in November we will have our residents of course, the emblematic duo MOONKIZA ready to give it their all as always. Our special guests will be the BMS crew that is increasingly gaining ground in the local scene giving free rein to the most infectious and addictive beats, leaving everyone always wanting more and more crazy partying. The warm up will be in charge of Markuss, who has been standing out in Barcelona in the Afro-House scene and his music is reaching important labels, being a young producer of great projection who debuts with us. You know, going out in winter on a Thursday requires desire, will and it is only achieved with passion for electronic music and dance, HEROES of the night that no season intimidates. You are one of them, right? Grab your best weapons and recharge your powers because we need you on the dance floor. There is a meeting only suitable for those who have the substance of urban HEROES! HEROES by Summer Heroes House, Tech-House, Afro-House, Deep-House, UK Garage, Acid-House
event_location_details: After the opening of Pacha Sitges in 1963 and Pacha Ibiza in 1973, Pacha Barcelona came to be one of the most renowned clubs in Spain. Now, it’s located in what is known as “Little Ibiza”, the closest zone to Port Olímpic. Pacha Barcelona got two indoor rooms (the main room and the Red Room) and a spectacular terrace with amazing sea views. There is where Pacha becomes a restaurant during the day, where you can enjoy the best Mediterranean cuisine and drink some cocktails while listening to the best deep house and chill out music. Basically, it’s like you were in a Beach Club in Ibiza. Honouring its name, Pacha Barcelona has become one of the best (if not the best club) in Barcelona. And, honouring the logo of the two cherries, it offers sweet, juicy and truly tempting experiences. Regarding the music, we're talking about a versatile club, now with its "Crazy Mondays" parties on Mondays, "Mad Tuesdays" on Tuesdays, “VICE” on Wednesdays, "La Juerga" on Thursdays, "Moulaga" on Fridays, "Pegao" on Saturdays and "SIGHT" on Sundays. Ranging from hits, reggaeton or hip-hop to the best house, deep house and techno in town, Pacha Barcelona attracts the best DJs in the world. The club has recently hosted C. Tangana, Bob Sinclar, Robbie Rivera, Claptone and, in nights hosted by Sight, underground electronic DJs like Sven Väth, Luciano or Davide Squillace. Pacha Barcelona isn’t just a club, it represents everything Pacha represents around the world: wherever you are, Pacha always offers the best parties and artists a city can offer. The place is very attractive, due to its casual and elegant atmosphere. This club is the big pearl among the nightclubs located at Barcelona’s Port Olímpic. It’s open 7 days a week and the most appropriate clothing is smart-casual, although for the SIGHT party on Sundays the access policy varies, giving a wider freedom of styles and letting the music be the protagonist. As we said, to have a careful look is something important to be able to access to Pacha Barcelona. Using the Xceed app, you can book your VIP table in advance.
location_address: Passeig Marítim de la Barceloneta, 38, Barcelona, Spain

event_location_details: Since its inception in 1953 Bikini has been an integral component of Barcelona nightlife scene. The venue hosts a very wide range of events: fashion shows, screenings, conventions and private and corporate parties. Its top notch sound system, its two rooms, together with an experienced team; make it a perfect spot to enjoy Barcelona nightlife and loosen up yourself a little bit. From live concerts of local and international music at Bikini you will certainly find what you are looking for.

Born to create unforgettable experiences, crossing its door transforms your night. Senses heighten, minds expand, and unparalleled acoustics elevate music to art. event_title: HEAVY HOUSE SOCIETY by SIDNEY CHARLES
line_up: Sidney Charles, Locklead, Luca Donzelli, Andrew Azara
venue_information: Sidney Charles has mastered the art of high impact house music that comes with a signature sense of depth, melody and groove. That unique style has made the Hamburg-born DJ, producer and label boss one of the underground's most prominent names: last year was his busiest ever with multiple chart-topping releases, high profile support from Radio 1 and standout gigs across the world. In 2024, the proven tastemaker will focus on his already influential Heavy House Society label with a series of HHS events taking place in locations worldwide. The last year has seen Sidney make an indelible mark on the scene. He played in Ibiza at the likes of Amnesia, DC10 and Cova Santa. He played to large crowds across several South American countries and all over the US from Miami to Las Vegas to New York and LA. He played in key Spanish cities at Input, Fabrik Madrid, Weekend Beach Festival, frequently visited Italy, played in the Netherlands multiple times a month and cemented his close relationship at UK hotbeds like Manchester's Warehouse Project and Leeds' Mint Warehouse. Whether playing to a close and compact crowd in a small basement or tearing up a vast festival main stage, Sidney knows how to join the dots between the past and the present. He manages to open up new house worlds with his educated selections but never forgets to blow up the dance floor in the process. Just like his productions, his DJ sets are full of surprises, twists and turns but also rooted in physical grooves. His love of jazz, hip hop and funk and his vast knowledge of the 90s sounds always shine through with plenty of heavy bass which makes the Sidney Sound so irresistible. Years after his first breakout hit, Sidney continues to reach the top of the charts with his newest creations. In 2023 there were two separate hits on different labels in Beatport's genre charts. Namely ‘Keep Rocking’ on Heavy House Society, and one of the biggest underground records of the year ‘House 2 Heal’ on Moxy Muzik, while he also released on the likes of Cécille, MicroHertz & PIV. Sidney's Heavy House Society is already a respected go-to outlet for solid and innovative house music. It mixes up releases from top-tier artists and well curated new school talents such as Kolter (aka Djoko), Ozzie Guven, Luuk Van Dijk, Locklead, Madvilla, M-High and many more. Sidney will be heading up the global Heavy House Society events with guest DJ’s curated from the label roster. He has solo releases in the works for the label as well as Solid Grooves, You&Me; and has a collaboration EP dropping with Kolter. All this is proof that Sidney Charles is at the top of his game. Social Links https://www.facebook.com/SidneyCharlesMusic https://www.instagram.com/sidneycharlesmusic/ https://twitter.com/SidneyCharlesM https://soundcloud.com/hurricane-kid
event_location_details: In the heart of Poble Espanyol lies INPUT High Fidelity Dance Club, the techno temple in Barcelona. Born to create unforgettable experiences, crossing its door transforms your night. Senses heighten, minds expand, and unparalleled acoustics elevate music to art. Its circular layout fosters intimacy, uniting diverse crowds in dance. Towering ceilings house a pulsating Funktion-One-based sound system, complemented by LED lights and cutting-edge AV tech for a psychedelic journey. Open Fridays, Saturdays, and select holidays from midnight till 6 am. Dress comfortably; trends don't matter—just bring sturdy shoes for the dance floor. Tickets available via Xceed or at the door, but advance booking saves money and time. With its stellar lineup, INPUT often sells out—don't miss out on the experience. Tip: Don't forget to follow INPUT on socials: @inputdanceclub (Instagram) and @inputbcn (TikTok)!

event_location_details: Since its inception in 1953 Bikini has been an integral component of Barcelona nightlife scene. Continuously evolving, constantly changing but always keeping the same spirit, Bikini is located between Sants and Sant-Gervasi neighborhoods (close to the city’s fancy street Diagonal). The venue hosts a very wide range of events: fashion shows, screenings, conventions and private and corporate parties. Its top notch sound system, its two rooms, together with an experienced team; make it a perfect spot to enjoy Barcelona nightlife and loosen up yourself a little bit. From live concerts of local and international music at Bikini you will certainly find what you are looking for.

event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

venue_information: CDLC offers the most exclusive night ambient. The atmosphere that results from mixing the best music, the trendiest people and excellent champagne can only be lived to the fullest at Carpe Diem Lounge Club. The most pleasant way to enjoy to the fullest CDLC is by savoring its two separated areas: The Bali Lounge and La Terraza Lounge. In the first you will be able to relax both during the day and the night, being delighted with CDLC staff full attention, enjoying food and drinks or simply the relaxed but always fashionable atmosphere. In the latter you can relax for a while in an elegant open air terrace, letting your senses be charmed by the presence of the sea.

If you want to enjoy the essence of electronic music that this city represents, without a doubt City Hall is the favorite option for visitors and residents, with an excellent location being in the heart of the city next to Plaça Catalunya, on Rambla Catalunya 2- 4.

event_title: Hypnotic By Slow Club: Frankie G + Bill Hates
event_genres: International, Live Music, House, Melodic House & Techno, Progressive
venue_information: Hypnotic Sessions will take us on a journey through acid sequences, explorations of new beat, progressive, melodic and underground house, tribal elements, touches of hypnotic techno, groovy beats, and breakbeat. A sonic flight for all tastes, a true Slow Xperience that invites you to let go and explore an uncharted yet introspective musical landscape, leading you to the most hidden recesses of your mind. Frankie G, one of the most iconic DJs of the Barcelona dance scene in the '90s. A renowned producer, he has collaborated with top artists in the global electronic scene such as Robbie Rivera, Cesar de Melero, Francesco Farfa, Tony Verdi, Paco Osuna, DJ Pippi, Simple Minds, Presuntos Implicados, Sally Olfield, Luis Bonias, Jordi Grau, Rebecca Brown… among others. On Saturday, October 5th, Glamour Freaks brings you a fresh edition of the HYPNOTIC party in The Jungle Boîte, where hypnotic sounds will take over once again! An authentic, rare themed night with grooves that of house music to techno. Sounds of Acid and drone. ★ FRANKIE G @dj.frankie_g BEATPORT@Frankie G SPOTIFY@Frankie G DISCOGS@Frankie G ★ BILL HATES @thebillhates SOUNDCLOUD@billhatesmusic Address: C/ de Paris 186, Barcelona. ***Grab your special eyeglasses of the HYPNOTIC event at the door! ***You will choose your drink preference (long drink or beer) upon entry, at the door.
event_location_details: La identidad de Slow Club que presenta una cuidada programación de calidad a cargo de sus residentes e invitados con la intención de hacernos viajar por el futuro, el pasado, y el presente y de la cultura de club. Los que no habéis venido nunca, tenéis que saber que Slow Club es un lugar bastante peculiar. El club está en el piso de arriba, y abajo tenemos la coctelería. El contraste del bailoteo desenfrenado bajo el techo luminoso del club y la distinción canalla del cocktail bar no recordamos haberla visto nunca antes.

event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

venue_information: London based artist, signed to Tuskegee, Crosstown Rebels and founder of the "Peculiar" party. If we followed Bas Ibellini around the world over the past few years, our memories might be stained with sweaty heaving crowds, beaches in Ibiza, dancefloors in New York, after-parties in London, and festivals in Mexico. In recent years, he has had the opportunity to perform at venerable night clubs including Fabric, DC10, Fuse Brussels and Output New York; alongside invitations to appear at key festivals including Sunwaves Romania and BPM in Mexico. A deep-rooted love for music, passed down from a musical family, has placed Bas in a fortunate position. Years of hard work, from pushing himself to become an expert turntablist as a youngster to putting on his own ‘Peculiar’ parties in East London, have laid the foundations for his growing success. When Bas isn't touring or in the studio, organising the perfect party for friends and booking world class acts is his passion. Previous guests have been Seth Troxler, The Martinez Brothers, Guy Gerber, The Mole, Herodot to name a few. On the production tip, Bas has taken a considered though enthusiastic tact, spending days on end toiling away in the studio. Learning the craft inside out, he prefers to take his time to release music. Over the last three years he has released on Seth Troxler and The Martinez Brothers’ Tuskegee imprint, and Damian Lazarus' Crosstown Rebels label.

Trikk is an internationally acclaimed producer and DJ, originally from Poro (Porugal) and now based in Berlin. His work with Dixon & Âme’s Innervisions label together with his busy touring schedule have launched him onto the global stage as par of the next gen of underground house music. With a consistent drip feed of biannual releases since 2011, Trikk has avoided the pressures of social media, rather focussing on a carefully considered output. This creation of space between producer and audience encourages the fow of new ideas, giving freedom to steer clear of the latest trends and expectations. With each release he aims to demonstrate his development as an arist, taking the time to properly digest infuences and inspirations. event_title: Les Enfants pres. Shonky All Night Long
event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: El ex-matemático, con el misterioso apodo – Shonky- se ha forjado un sonido característico, en un paisaje musical saturado, y ha logrado estar en la cúspide de una nueva era con el lanzamiento del sello y concepto Apollonia. Intercambio de un grado de matemáticas por un par de platos, Shonky admite que al principio no tenía idea de qué hacer con ellos. Un clubber dedicado desde su adolescencia, su primera acercamiento real a la escena underground como DJ se produjo en los afterhours Batofar de París. Fue allí donde descubrió su pasión por los sonidos house de San Francisco de los años 90, que en ese entonces pinchaba el residente Dan Ghenacia, y fue ese el comienzo de una amistad duradera, junto con su compañero parisino Dyed Soundorom. Ghenacia reconoció el don de Shonky para la producción desde el principio, “él es un talento natural, sé que cuando él hace algo, va a ser perfecto”, como sus primeros EP en Freak n’Chic Olympia, o su remezcla del track All I Can Say de Danton Eeprom. En 2008 lanzó su álbum debut Time Zone, mientras que los temas ‘Coco Feel & Love Shonk’ y ‘Roudor & Capulet’ marcaron un cruce de caminos musicales en su paso hacia un sonido nuevo – que reveló un house de dimensiones totalmente groovy infundido con voces hipnóticas. Así, pasaron años muy productivos con EPs para Crosstown Rebels, Contexterrior, Culprit y Real Tone. Después de haber pinchado en todo el mundo en clubes como Rex Club París, Space Ibiza, ARMA17 Moscow, Louche Leeds y Club Der Visionaere de Berlin, además de ser un invitado habitual en uno de sus clubes favoritos Panorama Bar, ahora es parte del recién formado proyecto Apollonia. Un sello concebido junto a Dan Ghenacia y Dyed Soundorom, el trío pincha vinilos back- to-back-to-back, generando exquisitos sets de cinco horas o más y presentándose en escenarios como DC10 Ibiza, Fabric London, Movement Torino y BPM Festival Mexico 2013, por nombrar sólo algunos. Como sello, Apollonia se encuentra en la su sexta entrega en los que Shonky ha participado con un EP en solo, The Minneapolis Touch, con el éxito de verano 2012 Close To The Edge, junto a Dan y en Trinidad, el primer EP del trío lanzado en julio de 2013.

event_title: Jackies pres. La Terrrazza Closing Party with Terrence Parker & Cody Currie
venue_information: HORARIO de 22:00 a 4:00am De forma extraordinaria, este año La Terrrazza abrirá sus puertas en noviembre, y tenemos el placer de organizar su gran Closing Party. Después de una larga temporada de impresionantes eventos al aire libre, nos reunimos por última vez este año en el icónico club La Terrrazza para celebrar la vida y el House en su esencia más pura. Será una noche única donde despediremos la temporada con la mejor energía y una selección musical impecable. Aprovecha esta oportunidad final para bailar bajo las estrellas al ritmo del mejor House del planeta. JACKIES is an independent House Music label from Barcelona and one of the most groundbreaking and incredible parties in the city. We bet on quality music. We believe in the transformative value of House music as a uniting axis between communities. After 5 years of history, we have had the pleasure of holding legendary parties in the main electronic music capitals of the world as Barcelona with our residency at La Terrrazza and W Hotel or in winter at Tunnel, in New York at the legendary Musica NYC club located in Manhattan, Miami at its famous music week, Amsterdam with our annual appointment at ADE on a boat with Louie Vega, in London at Egg or W Hotel, in Ibiza at Eden sharing the same space as Defected, in Tulum at the legendary Vagalume, Marbella in summer, Madrid and in our beloved Medellin, among others. We love to dance in summer under the light of the sun and the moon in open air spaces, and we take refuge under the bass of a club in winter. We welcome you to dance to the rhythm of House Music without rest, with top-level artists. Turn off the phone, forget your daily problems and connect with our magical ritual with the best House Music. Artists we have worked with: Louie Vega, Moodymann, Dennis Ferrer, Todd Terry, Richy Ahmed, Steve Lawler, Christian Smith house set, Sam Divine, The Shapeshifters, Davide Squillace, Catz n'Dogz, Kevin Saunderson, among others. Clubs: La Terrrazza Barcelona, ​​Pacha Barcelona, Musica Nyc, ​​Eden Ibiza, Vagalume Tulum, Supperclub boat Amsterdam, Mogli Marbella, Egg London, to name just a few. Don't forget to follow our renowned weekly podcast with more than 15K monthly listens we select and promote the best international/national artists of the genre.
event_location_details: La Terrrazza is an incredible open-air club, located inside the beautiful walled replica village (Pueblo Español) nestled at the side of Barcelona’s famous Montjuic Hill. The venue hosted masses of international DJs since it opened 20 years ago. It was often named within the top 50 best clubs in the world and is open only during the summer season, from May until October. House, electronica and techno, with a taste of Balearic sounds, are the main musical genres one can expect at its fantastic parties. Between the many famous names which have played here, the ones worthy of mention include Richie Hawtin and Ricardo Villalobos. Entry +18 years of age. The club reserves the right of admission.

event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

event_title: Les Enfants Brillants pres. Ron Bacardi a.k.a Ben Sims
event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: Ben Sims is one of techno’s most exciting talents - a DJ who has stayed true to the genre’s funk, groove and electronic fused origins whilst continuing to embrace and nurture its development over the past 25 odd years. Schooled on a diet of Hip Hop, Reggae, Soul, House and Rave in the 80’s, he played a huge part in defining British dance music in the 90s and continues to be an ardent champion of new music, producers and DJs via his many nights, record labels, radio shows, podcasts and relentless touring endeavors. As a DJ, Sims commands your attention, both visually and musically with anything from 3 to 5 decks running near constantly and hands, faders, effects and EQs a blur as tunes overlap to create a dense and quickly evolving collage of sound. Whether playing to 50, 500, or 5000 this unbridled energy and commitment to the art of mixing never falters and shows why Sims is regarded as one of the true masters on the circuit, both a DJ’s DJ and a straight-up party rocker in equal measures. In the studio, Sims has notched up over 50 original productions as well as countless remixes and edits in the past two decades. Embraced by techno’s originators and Detroit ambassadors he’s been, uniquely for a UK artist, called upon by Jeff Mills, Robert Hood and Kevin Saunderson for remixes as well as contributing to the majority of influential European labels from Mote Evolver to Drumcode to Cosmic to Token via Tresor, CLR, and his own (now completed) Theory imprint. Most recently, his disco/house leanings have birthed Ron Bacardi, an alias that has quickly established itself and resulted in 12”s dropping on Bass Culture, Karlovak, Way Back Wednesday and Hardgroove. Outside of the studio and club, the dedication, enthusiasm and search for the next great record/ talent continues. His monthly Run it Red radio show on NTS Live is devoted to new music, his club night, Machine (co-founded with Kirk Degiorgio), was set up to only showcase new music and his label activities, currently taking in Symbolism and Hardgroove, continue to provide rock solid platforms for new producers whilst also showcasing his own studio experiments. Never resting on his laurels, Sims continues to challenge himself at every turn. From a succession of dynamic b2b sets with other highly respected Techno DJs like DVS1, James Ruskin, ROD or Truncate, through his small-room b2b club night Kabuki, countless label/release projects, or a devotion to actively seeking out interesting club nights to play alongside the tried and tested, there’s always something fresh to get excited about with Ben Sims and you can trust that when the current boom (and its converts) move on, he’ll still be here, doing his thing and pushing his vision of techno.

With a curated music line-up that encompasses emerging talent and international guests from the underground scene the downtown club has become the meeting point for electronic music lovers with a passion for the clean sound and solid sound systems.

venue_information: HEX is back in Barcelona to take over AlteratE Club! Step into a world of merciless TechnoMetal, where Techno is not just Hard but HEAVY! At HEX, we don't just host events; we craft HEXperiences. Imagine a night where sounds paint tales of a dystopian future, a safe space where you're surrounded by a community who revel in the enigmatic. HEX is where the unconventional takes center stage, where night creatures unite to break free once more. HEX is a rebellion against the ordinary. Come as you are, embrace your uniqueness, and become part of the Movement. ----- **ARTIST LINEUP** 4 Heavy Techno & TechnoMetal artists set to rule the night: *LORENZO RAGANZINI* TechnoMetal devil Co-founder of HEX Techno Movement and the mastermind behind the TechnoMetal revolution. Lorenzo's fusion of Techno and Heavy Metal is set to ignite the HEX Barcelona event. *PAOLO FERRARA* TechnoMetal shaman Co-founder of HEX Techno Movement and a resident DJ. Paolo's sets blend heavy Techno with epic emotional moments, shaping tracks into timeless pieces of art. *LESTRANGE b2b BENEFICE* The two artists behind unforgettable tracks like “Sweet Dreams” and “The Beautiful People” are joining forces for a special b2b set, never before seen in Barcelona. *HANI* Barcelona's gem Hani, a staple of the HEX Team, will set the bar high right from the start. Don’t miss her set. ----- **THE VENUE** AlteratE Club, an intimate yet industrial space at Av. del Carrilet, 235, offers the ideal backdrop for this sonic odyssey, boasting top-notch sound quality. ----- **RUNNING ORDER** 23:59 - 01:30 - Hani 01:30 - 03:00 - LeStrange b2b Benefice 03:00 - 04:30 - Lorenzo Raganzini 04:30 - 06:00 - Paolo Ferrara ----- **TICKET INFO** We strongly recommend purchasing online pre-sale tickets here to ensure your entry. If door entry is denied, write us here https://www.hex-technomovement.com/home-1#contact-section for a next-day refund. Before buying, make sure you align with HEX values: freedom and safety above all. Respect our community. Feel the vibe, break the mold, be part of the HEX movement.

event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: Julien Veniel, artist name D’Julz, is a true craftsman behind the decks whose true strongest skill is his ability to go beyond mere genres and trends, deciding instead to actively shape the ever-changing soundscape of electronic music through his own productions, DJ performances and parties. Through a career spanning three decades, D’Julz has practically done it all. He began spinning in Paris, often playing his home city’s much-talked about early 90’s raves and legendary clubs, all before moving to New–York in 1993 to further hone his skills and cement his reputation as a true taste-maker in his field. The rest, as they say, is history. Despite finding himself in high demand in every corner of the globe, from the States to Japan and countless countries in between, D’Julz has always remained true to his roots in Paris, where he has been running the now legendary “Bass Culture” night at Rex club since 1997. In tandem with the birth of his party D’Julz has dedicated a large amount of time and energy into the production side of his musical output. Solo-wise his music has been signed to some of the world’s finest underground labels – Circus Company, Robsoul, Ovum, Rekids, 20:20 Vision and more. Since D’Julz started producing he has been responsible for a long list of tracks and remixes that have become essential weapons in the record boxes of the world’s DJ elite. As a DJ he exudes class and panache. A gifted curator of music whose pedigree has earned him a loyal international following and a constant tour schedule which sees him travel the worlds major cities every week playing the best venues they have on offer. Not to mention the infamous Circoloco (DC10) where he has held a long-standing residency, taking charge of the main room and the world-renowned red terrace room several times each summer season. Each set demonstrating D’Julz’s uncanny ability to weave his penchant for dub elements into the house and techno sphere and rocking DC10 with potent groove and sultry rhythms. D’Julz remains as enthusiastic as he was when he first started DJing, as his Bass Culture label goes from strength to strength, clocking over 50 releases and he continues to traverse the globe rocking dance floors every weekend. A true legend and one who will continue to be at the top of his game…

event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

event_location_details: In the heart of Poble Espanyol lies INPUT High Fidelity Dance Club, the techno temple in Barcelona. Born to create unforgettable experiences, crossing its door transforms your night. Senses heighten, minds expand, and unparalleled acoustics elevate music to art. Its circular layout fosters intimacy, uniting diverse crowds in dance. Towering ceilings house a pulsating Funktion-One-based sound system, complemented by LED lights and cutting-edge AV tech for a psychedelic journey. Tip: Don't forget to follow INPUT on socials: @inputdanceclub (Instagram) and @inputbcn (TikTok)!

event_title: Half Baked pres. Praslea + Sam Bangura
event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: The always tasteful Half Baked crew looks to one of their own for this fresh slice of delicious minimal. Sam Bangura was a new young resident for the party back in 2018 and since then has really honed his own sound. It’s laid bare here across four fine cuts, with opener ‘Range Finder’ serving up bristling drum machine grooves and cheeky basslines overlaid with cosmic chords. ‘Axel’s Limp’ is a brilliantly vibrant melodic overload with scintillating drums and plenty of neon colours.

event_title: ninkasi Showcase pres Dr. Banana & Melody
event_genres: Underground, International, Electro, House, Deep House
venue_information: Record connoisseur, label boss, and sleight-of-hand specialist – Dr. B promises a rabbit-hole record bag, labrador-like energy, and a light-hearted, left-field approach to the dance. Dr.B’s roots are in UKG, growing a globally-recognised label slinging out toasty cuts from new producers and re-issues from the golden era, but this is just a slither of the London-born DJ’s eclectic collection. You only need to flick through his recent bumper to bumpers to see how far and wide he can go. Whether it’s meaty chunks of electro, techno, and minimal with Evan Baggs, cross-genre party starters alongside Bradley Zero, straight shellers with Interplanetary Criminal, or just throwing it down alone, he’ll bring a bag of belters whatever the weather, wherever the crowd. After establishing himself as one of the UK’s most in-demand selectors, the London-born DJ has taken operations worldwide. From the floating intimacy of Berlin’s Hoppetosse to the sheer scale of Glastonbury, Fabric’s brutal brickwork to the iconic caverns of Kiev’s Art Club Closer and Mkvtvarse in Georgia – local, national, and global venues are the workshops for Dr. B’s versatile trotters. If he’s not getting his stirling’s worth out of a treasured travel pillow, playing venues and festivals across the UK and beyond, you’ll find him shooting three-pointers, digging into next week, or kickin’ it in front of the box with a moderately-priced pho.

event_title: (DAY EVENT) Elektronic Delight presents Betoko & Magnetizm
event_genres: International, Urban, Melodic House & Techno, Techno
line_up: Betoko, Magnetizm, Jairo Uría, Miss Manu, Simon Boulind, HannahLuyah
venue_information: Elektronic Delight bids farewell to the year with its last party of 2024 at Les Enfants Club. Get ready for an unforgettable evening on Saturday 21st of December, where electronic music will be the star, with a luxury line-up to close the year in style: BETOKO One of the most respected producers on the scene, Betoko has conquered the dancefloors with his deep house and tech house style from decades. With releases on labels such as Diynamic, Get Physical and his own Oko Recordings, the London-based Mexican artist has put his stamp on global electronica. His sets are a perfect blend of melody and rhythm, transporting the audience to a sonic experience that leaves no one indifferent. MAGNETIZM Magnetizm is an exciting duo of producers and DJs, hailing from the vibrant music scenes of Ibiza and London, they hold a residency at Cova Santa Ibiza. Their sound goes from Melodic House & Techno, Deep, Organic with a hint of afro house. JAIRO URÍA B2B MISS MANU Elektronic Delight's resident duo return with a back-to-back that promises to be very special. Jairo Uría and Miss Manu combine the best of their styles in an explosive performance, full of surprises, hypnotic beats and enveloping melodies. Their sets have marked some of the most memorable moments at Elektronic Delight parties, and this time will be no exception. BETERLATE B2B HANNALUYAH Two talents from the local scene come together to offer a vibrant and energetic set. Beterlate and Hannaluyah have carved a niche for themselves on the Barcelona electronic scene thanks to their ability to fuse the best of house and techno with a fresh and unique twist. Saturday December 21st, from 5pm to 11pm, join us at Les Enfants Club for a magical evening full of irresistible beats and a unique atmosphere. The best Day Clubbing in Barcelona is waiting for you to say goodbye to the year as it deserves: with quality electronic music, good vibes and an energy that you won't find anywhere else. Don't miss our last party of the year and let's make it unforgettable!
event_location_details: In the heart of Barcelona, Les Enfants Brillants arises as a club that stands out for its intimate atmosphere and sound quality accompanied by a hi-fi experience designed for the passionate. With a curated music line-up that encompasses emerging talent and international guests from the underground scene the downtown club has become the meeting point for electronic music lovers with a passion for the clean sound and solid sound systems.

event_title: PRISM Hard x KOMPOUND pres. 753 ‘All Night A/V Show’
venue_information: 753 is a duo from Barcelona with an enormous passion for hard techno music and audiovisual arts. Their goal is to do something different and creative they can be proud of. The name 753 comes from an 11th century samurai code of honor that inspired an entire nation to fight for its ideals. This code lives on in our world of constant change: through discipline, honor and loyalty, the code lasted in the memory of humanity until it became the legacy of 753. The 753 duo produces hard techno. They intend to innovate that scene and show what they are capable of. The people who discover them really appreciate their work and style, and as a result they have been able to work with record labels such as Gomboc, Hard Vision, Definition Of Hard techno, Märked, SCTR.
event_location_details: In the heart of Poble Espanyol lies INPUT High Fidelity Dance Club, the techno temple in Barcelona. Born to create unforgettable experiences, crossing its door transforms your night. Senses heighten, minds expand, and unparalleled acoustics elevate music to art. event_location_details: Since it opened its doors in 2001, Sutton Barcelona always played a leading role in Barcelona’s nightlife. From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.

event_title: SUW Disco Riders with Pablo Bozzi
line_up: Pablo Bozzi, Diego Montiel, Jessica Bellomo, John Justicia
venue_information: This season, we’re taking you on a journey through the finest in electro, indie dance, dark disco, techno grooves, EBM, and breaks. We’re bringing together some of the world’s top club residents and local legends who are shaking up the scene. Get ready for an unforgettable night as SUW takes over Sala Upload with a lineup that promises to deliver one of the biggest events of the year. You’ll be treated to a seamless blend of genres—from techno and electro to dark disco, EBM, and breaks—all carefully selected to create a night you won’t forget. Leading the charge is Pablo Bozzi, the master of Italo disco, modern techno, and EBM fusion. His sets bring together the best of the past and the future, creating an atmosphere that’s both nostalgic and forward-thinking—a true experience that takes the dancefloor to another level. Supporting Bozzi, we’ve got a killer lineup of local legends and rising stars: Diego Montiel – The visionary behind SUW, delivering deep grooves and eclectic rhythms that are guaranteed to light up the crowd. Iba Boo – Known for her genre-bending sets, she’ll guide the dancefloor through a wild ride of dark disco and electro. Jessica Bellomo – An Italian-Argentine artist making waves in the underground, blending dark disco, breaks, and industrial sounds with a touch of rock. She’s been leaving her mark across South America and Europe, and her sets are pure energy. John Justicia – A Barcelona favorite, known for high-energy performances that keep the night alive with a wide range of sounds. Raver Tips for an epic night: Be yourself: The dancefloor is all about self-expression—bring your authentic energy and let loose. Take care of your tribe: Stay connected with your crew, look out for each other, and keep the vibes high together. Stay energized: Hydrate, take breaks, and keep the good energy flowing all night. Embrace the moment: Every beat, every step, every connection is what makes the night unforgettable—soak it all in. Don’t miss out on this epic night—a true celebration of underground culture at one of Barcelona’s most iconic venues. Let’s end 2024 on a high note! GET YOUR TICKET! NOS VEMOS EN EL DANCEFLOOR! #SUWDiscoRiders #PabloBozzi #TechnoVibes #WeAreUnderground #BarcelonaRaves #EndOfYearParty

event_title: KINYXX - 2nd Anniversary - Fet!sh Edition at Nitsa Club
venue_information: Han sido dos años maravillosos. KINYXX nació como un espacio seguro para expresarse y ser libre, hasta convertirse en la fiesta queer y fetichista de referencia en Barcelona, donde cada persona puede perderse en su propio mundo, celebrando amor, expresión y aceptación en una pista inclusiva. Este segundo aniversario será en el mítico club Nitsa de Sala Apolo, la mejor sala clubbing de Barcelona. . Location: Sala Astin en Nitsa Club Welcome to kinyxx community. We are a openminded and inclusive Barcelona based electronic music party. From House to techno. So why kinyxx? Kinyxx is the new temple to freedom in the city, a place to express yourself freely in a safe environment with other like-minded party-goers without the fear to be jugded. Come to lose yourself in your own world feeling out the rhythm of the music while focus of the communion that is our dancefloor. Dancefloor is celebration of love, expression, acceptance, and community. We want you to come and party with family, friends, lovers and everyone is welcomed in our house. Age, body type, faith, race & gender, everybody is equal on the dancefloor. We support empowering your soul, create your true self, embrace your body and share your freedom. DRESSCODE MANDATORY (ALL THIS OPTIONS ARE VALID): All black clothes, latex, black, harness, chap, chains, pvc, vinyl, fancy lingerie, bondage, fishnet, mesh, rope, kilts, chain dress, cross dress, drag, fet!sh fantasy costume, full military uniform, k!nky, gothic, s3x kitten, doggies, cosplay, bodypaint, fantasy, sexy outfit, superheroes, etc.. **Rules of the house (if you are not agree with them, you are not welcome in our house)*** -Love and respect is our first rule. -Fet!sh dresscode is mandatory for this event. -Be brave and express yourself. -You can participate and be part of the show if you are invited. -Always look up and be kind with each other. -We do not accept any kind of phobia at our home. -Don’t jugde or laught of others. -Always ask for permission cuz you freedom end where the other start. -Keep clean every space we want everyone to feel home. -Don’t touch our performance without their permission. -If you see someone having a bad trip or bad behavior please contact the crew. -And don’t forget dancefloor is our temple.

From the very beginning, their parties were in everybody’s chats, both young and not so young people from the upper area in town. Located in the middle of Carrer Tuset, the club always knew what it wanted to be: a meeting point for forever friends, for those who want to have fun with their lifelong friends in a familiar club, cosy and true to a musical style always liked by the biggest audiences. Sutton Barcelona breathes a youthful, but mature atmosphere. Minimum age of 21 years old is required, although the public is usually around 23 or 25, even reaching 40 depending on the party. It's not weird to see public figures of high relevance in Sutton, such as actors, elite athletes or football players, fashion designers or politicians. Sutton Barcelona is one of the most exclusive clubs in the city and VIP people know it. You only need to take a look at some of the pictures of their Facebook albums or attend some of their big parties, such as Halloween or New Year's Eve, to discover their high-end style. Sutton Barcelona gives a remarkable prominence to music. The position of the DJ booth enhances the DJ to the audience and makes it a central figure of the event, although many times the sound is borne by resident artists. Commercial electronic music (mainly electro-house, dance and big room) sets the pace, although the R'n'B and the hits have their glorious moments as well. Despite this, Sutton has lived historic nights with huge names such as David Guetta, Galantis, The Martinez Brothers, Gianluca Vacchi or even Bruno Mars. You always have to keep an eye on their agenda and line-up before jumping into their booking options. Sutton always warns that you will be a victim of their pics. We don't know if that's the reason, but the required dress code is elegant, smart-casual. You don't need to wear a smart jacket or a long dress, although if you do, you won't be an exception. A well-fitting shirt, a good set and good shoes are enough (but essential) if you don't want, both boys and girls, be rejected. There's always quite a big line in the door of Sutton Barcelona. Almost every day it opens. And the ticket always costs 15 or 20€. That's why we are here. With the Xceed app, you can always sign up to the guest list before going to the club to get in for free. If you love to start the weekend quite soon, you are lucky, because Sutton is your party venue. Sutton opens from Wednesday to Saturday. With no exception. In addition to all the holidays eves, of course. Its schedule is the usual one in nightclubs: it opens at midnight and closes at 6 am, closing maybe at 5:30 am on Wednesdays and Thursdays, depending on the number of people partying inside.
